[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] It gives your agents real-time access to business data through open-source, type-safe connectors, managed credentials, and low-latency search.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Use it as a cloud platform or import connectors directly into your own agents.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Learn what the product is, choose the right interface, or jump straight into building.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Understand the building blocks: the Connect-Ask-Act model, agent operations, the Context Store, and system architecture.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Choose how to work with your data: the web app, MCP server, Python SDK, or HTTP API.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Browse the catalog of open-source connectors that equip agents to call third-party APIs.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Manage billing, plans, payments, usage monitoring, and subscription changes.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Consolidate data from hundreds of sources into your data warehouses, data lakes, and databases.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Then, move data into the operational tools where work happens.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Create connections, build custom connectors, and start syncing data in minutes.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Browse over 600 sources and destinations, and learn to set them up.
[src:airbyte-integration/docs-airbyte-com] Self-Managed versions release regularly.
